column5: Anyone have a update on the Taylor Island to Chamberlin area? Is the water level up at the Rags? Thanks
If you click on this link and look at the chart, you'll see that the water level is in the center of the graph which means about average.https://www.lwcb.ca/pdf/LacSeulGraph2019.06.07.pdf
It was spotty a couple weeks ago. Picked up better now as the shiners have moved in shallow. Headed up the 13th. Rags should be no problem.
went thru the rags with houseboat yesterday
